Content grants_funding: 
	Brad's nerves beginning to settle in. He wants to tell Ned about how stressed he is with the pressure of this research but recognizes the amount of time and money that has been put into this. Between the grants and the funding, Brad thinks about the thousands of dollars spent so that he can conduct this research. He needs to show that the resources given to him are being put to good use. Brad takes out papers and begins to display his work. 
	
	Ned leans back in his chair, giving Brad a look of concern. Brad realizes the slight tremble in his voice as well as the even less subtle shake in his hand. As he begins to change topics, Ned interrupts and asks “Brad, are you alright? You seem a bit frazzled.”
[end]
