Content dissapointed_feeling: 
	Brad's nerves beginning to settle in.  "I just don't think I'm handling all of this well," Brad confesses. "I feel like you’re disappointed in me with the way I'm working on these responsibilities."
	
	Ned interrupts, holding up a warning index finger, "Before you start doubting yourself, we need to focus on the task at hand. You've managed to progress this far, which you should be proud of. People handle pressure differently, Brad. These insecurities you're feeling, they're not an indication of your research abilities, they're merely a part of the process. Plus, you've made considerable progress, so why not see it through? Who knows? You might even impress yourself."
[end]
