Content frazzled: 
	“Yeah,” says Brad, “I’m just a bit stressed, that’s all!” Ned gives one last look of concern before Brad continues to explain his findings. When he finishes, Ned continues to study him before speaking. "You've clearly put a lot of work into this Brad," he says, pausing for a long moment. Brad feels as though his insecurties are confirmed by the unspoken criticism, but is determined not to show his fear. “Everything look great Brad,” says Ned, “Keep up the good work.” 
	As he walks out of Ned's office, the unheard criticism lingers in the back of his mind. Was Ned disappointed in his work but didn’t want to hurt his feelings? Is this actually good work? Or is he just barely making the cut?
[end]
